    "body": "## 📌 Description\n\n`cudaStreamSynchronize` in `CutlassGroupwiseScaledGEMMSM120` breaks CUDA graph capture and will fail explicitly starting CUDA 13.0.\n\n**Changes:**\n- Removed `cudaStreamSynchronize(stream)` and associated error handling from `gemm_groupwise_sm120.cuh` (lines 174-178)\n- Added `torch.cuda.synchronize()` calls in `tests/gemm/test_groupwise_scaled_gemm_fp8.py` after GEMM operations to ensure results are ready before assertions\n- Aligns SM120 implementation with SM100 patterns which don't synchronize after `gemm.run(stream)`\n\nThis approach follows separation of concerns: the kernel implementation remains asynchronous and CUDA graph compatible, while tests explicitly synchronize when needed to verify results.\n\n## 🔍 Related Issues\n\n\n\n## 🚀 Pull Request Checklist\n\n### ✅ Pre-commit Checks\n\n- [x] I have installed `pre-commit` by running `pip install pre-commit` (or used your preferred method).\n- [x] I have installed the hooks with `pre-commit install`.\n- [x] I have run the hooks manually with `pre-commit run --all-files` and fixed any reported issues.\n\n## 🧪 Tests\n\n- [x] Tests have been added or updated as needed.\n- [x] All tests are passing (`unittest`, etc.).\n\n## Reviewer Notes\n\nChanges include:\n1. **Kernel implementation** (6-line deletion): Removes blocking synchronization that prevents graph capture\n2. **Test updates**: Adds explicit synchronization in `test_fp8_blockscale_gemm`, `test_fp8_groupwise_gemm`, and `test_fp8_groupwise_group_gemm` to ensure GPU operations complete before assertions\n\nThis maintains forward compatibility with CUDA 13.0 while ensuring test correctness.\n\n<!-- START COPILOT ORIGINAL PROMPT -->\n\n\n\n<details>\n\n<summary>Original prompt</summary>\n\n> In the file `include/flashinfer/gemm/gemm_groupwise_sm120.cuh`, the function includes a `cudaStreamSynchronize` line that breaks CUDA graph capture. This will become problematic starting from CUDA 13.0 as such operations are explicitly checked for errors. To maintain forward compatibility and ensure functionality with graph-based workloads, it is necessary to remove the `cudaStreamSynchronize` line from this file.\n\n\n</details>\n\n\n\n<!-- START COPILOT CODING AGENT SUFFIX -->\n\n*This pull request was created from Copilot chat.*\n>\n\n<!-- START COPILOT CODING AGENT TIPS -->\n---\n\n✨ Let Copilot coding agent [set things up for you](https://github.com/flashinfer-ai/flashinfer/issues/new?title=✨+Set+up+Copilot+instructions&body=Configure%20instructions%20for%20this%20repository%20as%20documented%20in%20%5BBest%20practices%20for%20Copilot%20coding%20agent%20in%20your%20repository%5D%28https://gh.io/copilot-coding-agent-tips%29%2E%0A%0A%3COnboard%20this%20repo%3E&assignees=copilot) — coding agent works faster and does higher quality work when set up for your repo.\n",
